♫  The gentle breeze carries my shouts away  ♫

61
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:37,312
♫  The amber scenery  ♫ 
 ♫  Appears as clear as yesterday  ♫

62
00:07:37,312 --> 00:07:39,200
♫  Reality unfolds before me  ♫ 
 ♫  As I grasp the future in my hands  ♫

63
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:43,120
 If we meet one day in the summer, 

64
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:46,339
 I'll come see you with a bunch of salvias. 

65
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:53,300
♫  Accompany me as I become my true self  ♫

66
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:53,964
 You can leave. 

67
00:07:53,964 --> 00:07:57,064
♫  The night sky stretches endlessly  ♫

68
00:07:57,064 --> 00:07:59,840
♫  My stubbornness grows wild  ♫

69
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:02,016
♫  I won't stop running forward  ♫

70
00:08:02,016 --> 00:08:05,368
♫  My silent dream is calling out to me  ♫

71
00:08:05,368 --> 00:08:11,040
♫  You're the key to all my dreams  ♫

72
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:16,180
♫  I'll accompany you  ♫ 
 ♫  As you become your true self  ♫

73
00:08:16,180 --> 00:08:19,360
♫  Our story is coming to life  ♫

74
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:23,660
Some of you still made mistakes 
 on such basic questions.

75
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,379
You shouldn't.

76
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:27,939
You should have learned that 
 in middle school.

77
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:33,140
Let's turn to page 52 of the book.

78
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,399
"Why not sing out loud and stroll at ease?"

79
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:48,179
"With a bamboo cane and straw sandals, 
 lighter than a horse, who's afraid?"

80
00:08:48,179 --> 00:08:53,360
Egg is good for our health.

81
